<http://www.semanticweb.org/erichapsion/ontologies/HondaMotoGP> rdf:type owl:Ontology ;
                                                                 owl:versionIRI <http://www.semanticweb.org/erichapsion/ontologies/21_07_2026/HondaMotoGP> ;
                                                                 owl:imports <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/bfo/2020/bfo-core.ttl> ;
                                                                 rdfs:comment """This is the current version of my MotoGP Reference Ontology. 
As it stands, quite a lot of work remains to be done:
Classes need definitions.
IRIs need to be assigned.
Motorcycle parts need to be added.
Ways parts can fail need to be added. 

The project was inspired by the crash at the Catalunya Grand Prix in which Johann Zarco was injured (as macabre as 'inspiration' sounds). The hope is that this ontology, in a mature version, can serve as a way of keeping track of the nature and rate of accidents in MotoGP (and other venues), making the sport safer for riders.""" .

